        <fieldset id="donate-info"  class="tabset_content front">
          <h2>How Your Donations Help</h2>
          <p class="donation_info">
            For almost 14 years, the W3C has been developing and hosting  
            <a href="http://www.w3.org/QA/Tools/">Web Quality Tools</a> used every day by millions of Web developers 
            and Web designers. All these tools are <strong>free</strong>, <strong>Open-Source</strong> and provides the web
            with a fair, reliable help in building web content that works now and will work in the future.
          </p>
          <p class="donation_info">
            Good tools cost a lot to develop, support, host and maintain: with your help, we can make the validators 
            better, faster, friendlier, and maintain a great, free service for all of the Web.
          </p>
          <p class="donation_info">
            Donations to this program will be used exclusively for the maintenance, hosting and development of our free
            validation tools and other similar open source projects.
          </p>
          <h2>Policies for this program</h2>
          <p class="donation_info">
          The Validator donation and sponsorship program are governed by terms matching those described in the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Consortium/supporter-policy#policy_misc">Miscellaneous section of the W3C Supporters Program policy</a>.</p>
          <h2>No money? No problem!</h2>
          <p class="donation_info">
            There are many other ways you can <a href="http://www.w3.org/Status#contribute">contribute</a> to the W3C Validator projects.
          </p>
